cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the evaluation of superpixel methods, which is a common task in computer vision. It may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category as superpixels are often used in multimedia applications. The paper proposes a new global regularity measure, which suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper addresses the non-robustness of existing metrics, which suggests that it may also belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
